<h1>Ivo Lukač</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://ilukac.com/now">ilukac.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Zagreb

Croatia
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Managing partner of Netgen
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I am building a sustainable globally oriented business with a great team based in Croatia
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
My fellow co-owners happen to be my best friends so I love to work with them.  As Mark Twain said that travelling is the best cure to bigotry, I love to connect with different people all over the world, learn form them and tell them about us.  I am trying to make a good example to younger generations that it is possible to live in Croatia but do work globally, hope to teach my kids all this one day.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
If I exclude luck, envy and judgment from my every day life I can be more positive, proactive and improve myself.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Touching the Void by Joe Simpson
</p>

